CINF.courseTitle: Special Topics in Computer Information Systems
CINF.courseDescription: This is an introductory-level course with varied content designed by faculty to delve into topics that are not typically taught in existing courses. The sophistication and rigor of the content is consistent with courses that are offered in the second or third year of study in the department.

CINF.subject: CINF
CINF.courseDescription: This course is an introduction to relational database systems, including requirements gathering, database design and modeling, normalization, implementation using an enterprise database management system, SQL programming and query optimization. An introduction to NoSQL databases is included. Offered annually, either fall or spring. Prerequisite: CSCI 111, CSCI 141, or CSCI 261 or permission of instructor.
